title.narrative: Girls and boys under age five have increased and more equitable access to better quality nutrition services for early detection and treatment of severe acute malnutrition.

description.narrative: With support from UNICEF, the number of children with severe acute malnutrition (SAM) treated increased from 206,673 (107,7470 girls) in 2018 to 237,123 (123,722 girls) in 2019, with a corresponding increase of coverage of SAM treatment from 77 to 91 percent between 2018 and 2019. The quality of SAM treatment improved with nutrition performance indicators within acceptable Sphere standards of 91 percent cure rate, 5.3 percent defaulter rate and 0.4 percent death rate compared to 88 percent cure rate, 7 percent defaulter rate and 0.6 percent death rate in 2018. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:10/02/2020
